<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB: 5000, 9100, 9200, 9300, 9400 - REMOVE AND INSTALL -
        STRIKER PIN
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>STRIKER PIN</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600567">Figure 67</hotlnk>
                for Items in parentheses unless otherwise noted.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600567" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1600559.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 67. Door Striker Pin</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LOCK PILLAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. DOOR STRIKER PIN 34 TO 50 FT-LBS. (46 TO 68 Nm)</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. TORX HEAD TOOL</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. SPACER SHIM</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The door striker pin (Item 2) mounted on the lock pillar (Item 1) provides for positive engagement
                with the door latch assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600568">Item 1, Figure 68</hotlnk>). Striker pin removal and installation requires a
                torx head tool (Item 3). Enlarged mounting hole in lock pillar permits adjustment.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600568" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1600560.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 68. Door Latch Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. DOOR LATCH ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a torx head tool (Item 3) to remove the door striker pin (Item 2) from the lock
                    pillar (Item 1).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If spacer shims (Item 4) are used between the lock pillar (Item 1) and the door striker
                    pin (Item 2), save and re-use during installation.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If door striker pin (Item 2) was removed, position the spacer shims (Item 4), if so
                    equipped, in place on the lock pillar (Item 1).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install door striker pin (Item 2) by threading it into the lock pillar (Item 1) with a
                    torx head tool (Item 3). Tighten to 34 to 50 ft-lbs. (46 to 68 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If door striker pin adjustment is required, refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16005v_77.xml" xrefid="x1600510">ADJUSTMENTS, STRIKER PIN AT LOCK PILLAR.
                        <xref refid="x1600510"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
